version_description:
- Changed Whoscall theme
- Enjoyed Christmas with Santa
- Wrapped some presents

Hope you all enjoyed the Christmas theme, lets embrace year 2016!

1. New page design for adding numbers to identified.
2. New tutorial for hiding Whoscall numbers, to let everybody know to do it :)
3. Fixed some issues and eliminated some bugs.

- Performance tweak for Identified
- Fixed some crash issues

- Performance improvement.
- Fixed some crash issues.

1. Redesign Identified UI and Top Spammers update mechanism.
2. Integrate "Favorites" into "My Identified List".
3. Function rename.

Fixed some crash issues

New in v1.6:
1. Redesign Identified UI and Top Spammers update mechanism.
2. Integrate "Favorites" into "My Identified List".
3. Function rename.

New update for iOS 10 ! 

■ Call identification
Identify information of incoming unknown calls instantly through tags reported by other users, internet search results, and our comprehensive global database. You decide whether to pick up the phone!

■ Block Calls
Block spam calls and never be bothered again. Get rid of pesky telemarketers and annoying robocalls

** Reminder **
- Call identification & blocking is only supported in iOS 10 or above and 64-bit devices (iPhone 5/5c/4s are not in supported list)
- Caller ID are only supported in the following countries: TW, KR, JP, HK, TH, BR, US, IN, ID, MY, and UK.

v2.0.1:
(1) Fixed crash issues.
(2) If you cannot find the "Caller Identification & Blocking" option in Settings or keep non-stop activating status, 
Please take the following solutions:
- Remove the "Settings" app from background (Multitasking) and activate again.
- If solution first one not work, please reboot your device and activate again.
- If both of above solutions failed, remove Whoscall app and try to install again.
